description:
src/lib.rs lines 60-152 contain two error-mapper fns. Across both, the pattern

    return SecretError::Backend {
        backend: "aws-ssm",
        source: e.into(),
    };

is repeated 7 times (lines 72, 79, 90, 113, 120, 131, 142) for different conditions. Each conditional then returns the same struct literal.

Fix: extract a small helper

    fn permanent(e: SdkError<E>) -> SecretError where ... {
        SecretError::Backend { backend: "aws-ssm", source: e.into() }
    }
    fn transient(e: SdkError<E>) -> SecretError where ... {
        SecretError::Unavailable { backend: "aws-ssm", source: e.into() }
    }

…or restructure each mapper as

    let kind = if se.is_some_and(...) { Kind::NotFound }
               else if se.is_some_and(...) { Kind::Permanent }
               else { Kind::Transient };

so the SecretError variant is built once per mapper.

Either rewrite is shorter and harder to mis-edit (e.g. accidentally dropping the `backend:` field for one branch).

This is a partial mirror of 8bh8.5 for secretx-aws-sm; aws-ssm has the same shape but the get/put mappers are not literally identical (the conditions differ), so the structural fix is per-mapper deduplication rather than cross-mapper unification.
